<A>__{we pull back to see james alone in the car. the road is crowded and manic; james is intense, hard, exhilarated, alert a hunter. the car is full of junk, pop cans, styrofoam containers, all suggesting that he has basically been living in the car for some time. james is searching for something among the lanes of traffic, threading the immense car in and out of the shifting holes that appear and disappear, driving with a fluid recklessness that is recognizably vaughan's style. suddenly, james becomes tense, focused: he has spotted what he has been looking for.}
